{"key":"processedPost-17838838","value":{"id":17838838,"first":17837770,"last":17840012,"when":1361423420,"utime":"02/21/13 07:10 AM","content":"It makes little difference, but I've found agar wedges tend to recover faster laying right on top of the grains rather than shaken in.&nbsp; This also allows contaminants that may have been introduced to show their ugly face if present.&nbsp; Once the mycelium grows off the wedge and into the first layer or two of grains, give it a shake.<br /><br />When inoculating with spores, don't shake until 20% to 30% colonization, and don't shake again until it's done.&nbsp; <br /><br />With grain to grain transfers, you can shake immediately or wait a day or two to shake.&nbsp; It might be a bit faster to wait, but not much.&nbsp; Do whatever is convenient.<br />RR","title":"Re: how often should i shake ?"}}